                 ClearWorks(TM) Enterprise Server
                       version 2.4 

   ClearWorks is a professional Lean R & D life-cycle management tool, it release the power of Scrum, XP and Kanban for agile process management.
This cdrom is a green run-time package, can up and running directly after uncompressed, no installation required. 

SYSTEM REQUIRES: 
----------------
Windows 2000/XP/Vista, Windows 2003 Server or Windows 2008 Server.

STEPS:
----------------

1, Uncompress clearworks_ee_win20.rar under the root of disk D:
   *** Note: must under the root of disk D: ! 

2, Enter D:\sevensoft, change the default language settings in clearworks.ini as bellow,
   defualt = en
   ;defualt = zh_CN
   the settings will change the UI localization.

3, Enter D:\sevensoft, click apache_start.bat and mysql_start.bat,
   start Web server and Mysql server.

4, Start your browser(IE, FireFox etc), enter:
   http://localhost/clearworks/index.html
   login name: administrator password: passwd
   Instant Message, username: admin Password: 123456 room1:123

5, Shutdown servers,
   execute apache_stop.bat and mysql_stop.bat.

** Important Note: 
   To reduce the size of download files, this package does not include the "FULL RUNTIME" of this software, including the embedded SVN server, workflow chart generate program (Graphviz) and the module that support source code management operations in web browser, because these files are too large that unsuitable for downloading, please contact us for more info. 
   In addition, the font files required by chart display are not included too, you can copy the font files by youself:   
   Font Name: Arial(TrueType)             File Name: ARIAL.TTF
   Font Name: Arial Bold(TrueType)        File Name: ARIALBD.TTF
   Font Name: SimHei(TrueType)            File Name: simhei.ttf
   Font Name: SimSun & NSimSun (TrueType) File Name: simsun.ttc

   Steps: 
   1) Control Panel -> Font -> File Name -> Select the font files -> click the "Edit" menu on top of the "Resource Explorer" of Windows.
   2) Go to the directory of D:\sevensoft\clearworks\lib\jpgraph\fonts, and select the "Paste" menu of the "Resource Explorer" of Windows.

